'''Lua Programming for the Creative ZEN X-Fi2''' is for those wishing to learn how to program custom applications in the '''Lua''' programming language for the '''Creative ZEN X-Fi2''' media player. It is intended for those with some knowledge of programming wishing to learn the Lua extension libraries that interface to the Zen X-Fi2's display, touch sensors, audio output, accelerometers, etc. This book is not intended as a general programming text, or a text on the common features of the Lua language. It is not intended as a substitute for the official API reference.
* ''For the basics of Lua, please see the project's home page: [http://www.lua.org/ The Programming Language Lua] * ''For the official description of the ZEN X-Fi2 Lua extension library, see Creative Labs' official page: [http://www.creative.com/zenxfi2/adk/ ZEN X-Fi2 Application Development Kit]
{{Subjects|Computing}}

